{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I live and work from Tokyo, Japan."},{"time":4000,"text":"And I specialize in human behavioral research,"},{"time":8000,"text":"and applying what we learn to think about the future in different ways,"},{"time":14000,"text":"and to design for that future."},{"time":16000,"text":"And you know, to be honest, I've been doing this for seven years,"},{"time":20000,"text":"and I haven't got a clue what the future is going to be like."},{"time":22000,"text":"But I've got a pretty good idea"},{"time":24000,"text":"how people will behave when they get there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"This is my office. It's out there."},{"time":31000,"text":"It's not in the lab,"},{"time":33000,"text":"and it's increasingly in places like India, China, Brazil, Africa."},{"time":42000,"text":"We live on a planet -- 6.3 billion people."},{"time":45000,"text":"About three billion people, by the end of this year,"},{"time":47000,"text":"will have cellular connectivity."},{"time":50000,"text":"And it'll take about another two years to connect the next billion after that."},{"time":55000,"text":"And I mention this because,"},{"time":57000,"text":"if we want to design for that future,"},{"time":59000,"text":"we need to figure out what those people are about."},{"time":61000,"text":"And that's, kind of, where I see what my job is"},{"time":63000,"text":"and what our team's job is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"Our research often starts with a very simple question."},{"time":69000,"text":"So I'll give you an example. What do you carry?"},{"time":73000,"text":"If you think of everything in your life that you own,"},{"time":78000,"text":"when you walk out that door,"},{"time":80000,"text":"what do you consider to take with you?"},{"time":82000,"text":"When you're looking around, what do you consider?"},{"time":85000,"text":"Of that stuff, what do you carry?"},{"time":88000,"text":"And of that stuff, what do you actually use?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"So this is interesting to us,"},{"time":93000,"text":"because the conscious and subconscious decision process"},{"time":97000,"text":"implies that the stuff that you do take with you and end up using"},{"time":100000,"text":"has some kind of spiritual, emotional or functional value."},{"time":103000,"text":"And to put it really bluntly, you know,"},{"time":106000,"text":"people are willing to pay for stuff that has value, right?"},{"time":110000,"text":"So I've probably done about five years' research"},{"time":113000,"text":"looking at what people carry."},{"time":115000,"text":"I go in people's bags. I look in people's pockets, purses."},{"time":119000,"text":"I go in their homes. And we do this worldwide,"},{"time":123000,"text":"and we follow them around town with video cameras."},{"time":126000,"text":"It's kind of like stalking with permission."},{"time":128000,"text":"And we do all this -- and to go back to the original question,"},{"time":132000,"text":"what do people carry?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":135000,"text":"And it turns out that people carry a lot of stuff."},{"time":137000,"text":"OK, that's fair enough."},{"time":139000,"text":"But if you ask people what the three most important things that they carry are --"},{"time":144000,"text":"across cultures and across gender and across contexts --"},{"time":148000,"text":"most people will say keys, money"},{"time":151000,"text":"and, if they own one, a mobile phone."},{"time":154000,"text":"And I'm not saying this is a good thing, but this is a thing, right?"},{"time":157000,"text":"I mean, I couldn't take your phones off you if I wanted to."},{"time":159000,"text":"You'd probably kick me out, or something."},{"time":164000,"text":"OK, it might seem like an obvious thing"},{"time":167000,"text":"for someone who works for a mobile phone company to ask."},{"time":169000,"text":"But really, the question is, why? Right?"},{"time":171000,"text":"So why are these things so important in our lives?"},{"time":174000,"text":"And it turns out, from our research, that it boils down to survival --"},{"time":178000,"text":"survival for us and survival for our loved ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182000,"text":"So, keys provide an access to shelter and warmth --"},{"time":187000,"text":"transport as well, in the U.S. increasingly."},{"time":190000,"text":"Money is useful for buying food, sustenance,"},{"time":194000,"text":"among all its other uses."},{"time":195000,"text":"And a mobile phone, it turns out, is a great recovery tool."},{"time":201000,"text":"If you prefer this kind of Maslow's hierarchy of needs,"},{"time":204000,"text":"those three objects are very good at supporting"},{"time":207000,"text":"the lowest rungs in Maslow's hierarchy of needs."},{"time":210000,"text":"Yes, they do a whole bunch of other stuff,"},{"time":212000,"text":"but they're very good at this."},{"time":214000,"text":"And in particular, it's the mobile phone's ability"},{"time":218000,"text":"to allow people to transcend space and time."},{"time":221000,"text":"And what I mean by that is, you know,"},{"time":223000,"text":"you can transcend space by simply making a voice call, right?"},{"time":228000,"text":"And you can transcend time by sending a message at your convenience,"},{"time":231000,"text":"and someone else can pick it up at their convenience."},{"time":234000,"text":"And this is fairly universally appreciated, it turns out,"},{"time":238000,"text":"which is why we have three billion plus people who have been connected."},{"time":241000,"text":"And they value that connectivity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"But actually, you can do this kind of stuff with PCs."},{"time":245000,"text":"And you can do them with phone kiosks."},{"time":248000,"text":"And the mobile phone, in addition, is both personal --"},{"time":252000,"text":"and so it also gives you a degree of privacy -- and it's convenient."},{"time":255000,"text":"You don't need to ask permission from anyone,"},{"time":257000,"text":"you can just go ahead and do it, right?"},{"time":261000,"text":"However, for these things to help us survive,"},{"time":265000,"text":"it depends on them being carried."},{"time":267000,"text":"But -- and it's a pretty big but -- we forget."},{"time":271000,"text":"We're human, that's what we do. It's one of our features."},{"time":274000,"text":"I think, quite a nice feature."},{"time":276000,"text":"So we forget, but we're also adaptable,"},{"time":281000,"text":"and we adapt to situations around us pretty well."},{"time":284000,"text":"And so we have these strategies to remember,"},{"time":286000,"text":"and one of them was mentioned yesterday."},{"time":288000,"text":"And it's, quite simply, the point of reflection."},{"time":291000,"text":"And that's that moment when you're walking out of a space,"},{"time":294000,"text":"and you turn around, and quite often you tap your pockets."},{"time":297000,"text":"Even women who keep stuff in their bags tap their pockets."},{"time":299000,"text":"And you turn around, and you look back into the space,"},{"time":302000,"text":"and some people talk aloud."},{"time":304000,"text":"And pretty much everyone does it at some point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"OK, the next thing is -- most of you, if you have a stable home life,"},{"time":311000,"text":"and what I mean is that you don't travel all the time, and always in hotels,"},{"time":314000,"text":"but most people have what we call a center of gravity."},{"time":317000,"text":"And a center of gravity is where you keep these objects."},{"time":321000,"text":"And these things don't stay in the center of gravity,"},{"time":323000,"text":"but over time, they gravitate there."},{"time":325000,"text":"It's where you expect to find stuff."},{"time":327000,"text":"And in fact, when you're turning around,"},{"time":328000,"text":"and you're looking inside the house,"},{"time":330000,"text":"and you're looking for this stuff,"},{"time":332000,"text":"this is where you look first, right?"},{"time":334000,"text":"OK, so when we did this research,"},{"time":338000,"text":"we found the absolutely, 100 percent, guaranteed way"},{"time":341000,"text":"to never forget anything ever, ever again."},{"time":344000,"text":"And that is, quite simply, to have nothing to remember."},{"time":349000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"OK, now, that sounds like something you get on a Chinese fortune cookie, right?"},{"time":354000,"text":"But is, in fact, about the art of delegation."},{"time":358000,"text":"And from a design perspective,"},{"time":360000,"text":"it's about understanding what you can delegate to technology"},{"time":365000,"text":"and what you can delegate to other people."},{"time":368000,"text":"And it turns out, delegation -- if you want it to be --"},{"time":370000,"text":"can be the solution for pretty much everything,"},{"time":374000,"text":"apart from things like bodily functions, going to the toilet."},{"time":377000,"text":"You can't ask someone to do that on your behalf."},{"time":379000,"text":"And apart from things like entertainment,"},{"time":382000,"text":"you wouldn't pay for someone to go to the cinema for you and have fun on your behalf,"},{"time":385000,"text":"or, at least, not yet."},{"time":387000,"text":"Maybe sometime in the future, we will."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"So, let me give you an example of delegation in practice, right."},{"time":394000,"text":"So this is -- probably the thing I'm most passionate about"},{"time":397000,"text":"is the research that we've been doing on illiteracy"},{"time":399000,"text":"and how people who are illiterate communicate."},{"time":401000,"text":"So, the U.N. estimated -- this is 2004 figures --"},{"time":405000,"text":"that there are almost 800 million people who can't read and write, worldwide."},{"time":409000,"text":"So, we've been conducting a lot of research."},{"time":413000,"text":"And one of the things we were looking at is --"},{"time":416000,"text":"if you can't read and write,"},{"time":418000,"text":"if you want to communicate over distances,"},{"time":420000,"text":"you need to be able to identify the person"},{"time":423000,"text":"that you want to communicate with."},{"time":425000,"text":"It could be a phone number, it could be an e-mail address,"},{"time":427000,"text":"it could be a postal address."},{"time":428000,"text":"Simple question: if you can't read and write,"},{"time":430000,"text":"how do you manage your contact information?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":432000,"text":"And the fact is that millions of people do it."},{"time":435000,"text":"Just from a design perspective, we didn't really understand how they did it,"},{"time":439000,"text":"and so that's just one small example"},{"time":441000,"text":"of the kind of research that we were doing."},{"time":444000,"text":"And it turns out that illiterate people are masters of delegation."},{"time":447000,"text":"So they delegate that part of the task process to other people,"},{"time":451000,"text":"the stuff that they can't do themselves."},{"time":454000,"text":"Let me give you another example of delegation."},{"time":456000,"text":"This one's a little bit more sophisticated,"},{"time":458000,"text":"and this is from a study that we did in Uganda"},{"time":460000,"text":"about how people who are sharing devices, use those devices."},{"time":464000,"text":"Sente is a word in Uganda that means money."},{"time":467000,"text":"It has a second meaning, which is to send money as airtime. OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":472000,"text":"And it works like this."},{"time":474000,"text":"So let's say, June, you're in a village, rural village."},{"time":477000,"text":"I'm in Kampala and I'm the wage earner."},{"time":481000,"text":"I'm sending money back, and it works like this."},{"time":484000,"text":"So, in your village, there's one person in the village with a phone,"},{"time":487000,"text":"and that's the phone kiosk operator."},{"time":488000,"text":"And it's quite likely that they'd have a quite simple mobile phone as a phone kiosk."},{"time":492000,"text":"So what I do is, I buy a prepaid card like this."},{"time":497000,"text":"And instead of using that money to top up my own phone,"},{"time":500000,"text":"I call up the local village operator."},{"time":502000,"text":"And I read out that number to them, and they use it to top up their phone."},{"time":506000,"text":"So, they're topping up the value from Kampala,"},{"time":508000,"text":"and it's now being topped up in the village."},{"time":511000,"text":"You take a 10 or 20 percent commission, and then you --"},{"time":514000,"text":"the kiosk operator takes 10 or 20 percent commission,"},{"time":517000,"text":"and passes the rest over to you in cash."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"OK, there's two things I like about this."},{"time":523000,"text":"So the first is, it turns anyone who has access to a mobile phone --"},{"time":528000,"text":"anyone who has a mobile phone --"},{"time":530000,"text":"essentially into an ATM machine."},{"time":532000,"text":"It brings rudimentary banking services to places"},{"time":535000,"text":"where there's no banking infrastructure."},{"time":537000,"text":"And even if they could have access to the banking infrastructure,"},{"time":540000,"text":"they wouldn't necessarily be considered viable customers,"},{"time":543000,"text":"because they're not wealthy enough to have bank accounts."},{"time":546000,"text":"There's a second thing I like about this."},{"time":549000,"text":"And that is that despite all the resources at my disposal,"},{"time":553000,"text":"and despite all our kind of apparent sophistication,"},{"time":555000,"text":"I know I could never have designed something as elegant"},{"time":559000,"text":"and as totally in tune with the local conditions as this. OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":564000,"text":"And, yes, there are things like Grameen Bank and micro-lending."},{"time":567000,"text":"But the difference between this and that"},{"time":569000,"text":"is, there's no central authority trying to control this."},{"time":573000,"text":"This is just street-up innovation."},{"time":578000,"text":"So, it turns out the street is a never-ending source of"},{"time":581000,"text":"inspiration for us."},{"time":583000,"text":"And OK, if you break one of these things here, you return it to the carrier."},{"time":587000,"text":"They'll give you a new one."},{"time":588000,"text":"They'll probably give you three new ones, right?"},{"time":590000,"text":"I mean, that's buy three, get one free. That kind of thing."},{"time":593000,"text":"If you go on the streets of India and China, you see this kind of stuff."},{"time":597000,"text":"And this is where they take the stuff that breaks,"},{"time":599000,"text":"and they fix it, and they put it back into circulation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605000,"text":"This is from a workbench in Jilin City, in China,"},{"time":609000,"text":"and you can see people taking down a phone"},{"time":611000,"text":"and putting it back together."},{"time":613000,"text":"They reverse-engineer manuals."},{"time":616000,"text":"This is a kind of hacker's manual,"},{"time":619000,"text":"and it's written in Chinese and English."},{"time":621000,"text":"They also write them in Hindi."},{"time":623000,"text":"You can subscribe to these."},{"time":626000,"text":"There are training institutes where they're churning out people"},{"time":629000,"text":"for fixing these things as well."},{"time":632000,"text":"But what I like about this is,"},{"time":635000,"text":"it boils down to someone on the street with a small, flat surface,"},{"time":641000,"text":"a screwdriver, a toothbrush for cleaning the contact heads --"},{"time":645000,"text":"because they often get dust on the contact heads -- and knowledge."},{"time":649000,"text":"And it's all about the social network of the knowledge, floating around."},{"time":653000,"text":"And I like this because it challenges the way that we design stuff,"},{"time":657000,"text":"and build stuff, and potentially distribute stuff."},{"time":659000,"text":"It challenges the norms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662000,"text":"OK, for me the street just raises so many different questions."},{"time":668000,"text":"Like, this is Viagra that I bought from a backstreet sex shop in China."},{"time":674000,"text":"And China is a country where you get a lot of fakes."},{"time":677000,"text":"And I know what you're asking -- did I test it?"},{"time":679000,"text":"I'm not going to answer that, OK."},{"time":681000,"text":"But I look at something like this, and I consider the implications"},{"time":685000,"text":"of trust and confidence in the purchase process."},{"time":688000,"text":"And we look at this and we think, well, how does that apply,"},{"time":690000,"text":"for example, for the design of -- the lessons from this --"},{"time":693000,"text":"apply to the design of online services, future services in these markets?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":700000,"text":"This is a pair of underpants from --"},{"time":704000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":706000,"text":"from Tibet."},{"time":708000,"text":"And I look at something like this, and honestly, you know,"},{"time":711000,"text":"why would someone design underpants with a pocket, right?"},{"time":714000,"text":"And I look at something like this and it makes me question,"},{"time":717000,"text":"if we were to take all the functionality in things like this,"},{"time":721000,"text":"and redistribute them around the body"},{"time":722000,"text":"in some kind of personal area network,"},{"time":724000,"text":"how would we prioritize where to put stuff?"},{"time":726000,"text":"And yes, this is quite trivial, but actually the lessons from this can apply to that"},{"time":730000,"text":"kind of personal area networks."},{"time":733000,"text":"And what you see here is a couple of phone numbers"},{"time":736000,"text":"written above the shack in rural Uganda."},{"time":739000,"text":"This doesn't have house numbers. This has phone numbers."},{"time":744000,"text":"So what does it mean when people's identity is mobile?"},{"time":750000,"text":"When those extra three billion people's identity is mobile, it isn't fixed?"},{"time":755000,"text":"Your notion of identity is out-of-date already, OK,"},{"time":759000,"text":"for those extra three billion people."},{"time":762000,"text":"This is how it's shifting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"And then I go to this picture here, which is the one that I started with."},{"time":769000,"text":"And this is from Delhi."},{"time":772000,"text":"It's from a study we did into illiteracy,"},{"time":775000,"text":"and it's a guy in a teashop."},{"time":777000,"text":"You can see the chai being poured in the background."},{"time":779000,"text":"And he's a, you know, incredibly poor teashop worker,"},{"time":783000,"text":"on the lowest rungs in the society."},{"time":785000,"text":"And he, somehow, has the appreciation"},{"time":789000,"text":"of the values of Livestrong."},{"time":791000,"text":"And it's not necessarily the same values,"},{"time":793000,"text":"but some kind of values of Livestrong,"},{"time":795000,"text":"to actually go out and purchase them,"},{"time":798000,"text":"and actually display them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800000,"text":"For me, this kind of personifies this connected world,"},{"time":802000,"text":"where everything is intertwined, and the dots are --"},{"time":806000,"text":"it's all about the dots joining together."},{"time":809000,"text":"OK, the title of this presentation is \"Connections and Consequences,\""},{"time":813000,"text":"and it's really a kind of summary of five years of trying to figure out"},{"time":818000,"text":"what it's going to be like when everyone on the planet"},{"time":821000,"text":"has the ability to transcend space and time"},{"time":824000,"text":"in a personal and convenient manner, right?"},{"time":827000,"text":"When everyone's connected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829000,"text":"And there are four things."},{"time":833000,"text":"So, the first thing is the immediacy of ideas,"},{"time":835000,"text":"the speed at which ideas go around."},{"time":838000,"text":"And I know TED is about big ideas,"},{"time":840000,"text":"but actually, the benchmark for a big idea is changing."},{"time":845000,"text":"If you want a big idea, you need to embrace everyone on the planet,"},{"time":849000,"text":"that's the first thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851000,"text":"The second thing is the immediacy of objects."},{"time":854000,"text":"And what I mean by that is, as these become smaller,"},{"time":858000,"text":"as the functionality that you can access through this becomes greater --"},{"time":862000,"text":"things like banking, identity --"},{"time":864000,"text":"these things quite simply move very quickly around the world."},{"time":869000,"text":"And so the speed of the adoption of things"},{"time":871000,"text":"is just going to become that much more rapid,"},{"time":873000,"text":"in a way that we just totally cannot conceive,"},{"time":876000,"text":"when you get it to 6.3 billion"},{"time":878000,"text":"and the growth in the world's population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881000,"text":"The next thing is that, however we design this stuff --"},{"time":885000,"text":"carefully design this stuff --"},{"time":886000,"text":"the street will take it, and will figure out ways to innovate,"},{"time":889000,"text":"as long as it meets base needs --"},{"time":892000,"text":"the ability to transcend space and time, for example."},{"time":895000,"text":"And it will innovate in ways that we cannot anticipate."},{"time":900000,"text":"In ways that, despite our resources, they can do it better than us."},{"time":903000,"text":"That's my feeling."},{"time":905000,"text":"And if we're smart, we'll look at this stuff that's going on,"},{"time":909000,"text":"and we'll figure out a way to enable it to inform and infuse"},{"time":914000,"text":"both what we design and how we design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917000,"text":"And the last thing is that -- actually, the direction of the conversation."},{"time":924000,"text":"With another three billion people connected,"},{"time":929000,"text":"they want to be part of the conversation."},{"time":931000,"text":"And I think our relevance and TED's relevance"},{"time":936000,"text":"is really about embracing that and learning how to listen, essentially."},{"time":942000,"text":"And we need to learn how to listen."},{"time":943000,"text":"So thank you very, very much."},{"time":945000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}